#: ../../L/life.rst:5
msgid "life"
msgstr "life"

#: ../../L/life.rst:7
msgid "n\\."
msgstr "名詞"

#: ../../L/life.rst:10
#, python-format
msgid ""
"A cellular-automata game invented by John Horton Conway and first introduced"
" publicly by Martin Gardner (*Scientific American*\\, October 1970); the "
"game's popularity had to wait a few years for computers on which it could "
"reasonably be played, as it's no fun to simulate the cells by hand. Many "
"hackers pass through a stage of fascination with it, and hackers at various "
"places contributed heavily to the mathematical analysis of this game (most "
"notably Bill Gosper at MIT, who even implemented life in :ref:`TECO`\\!). "
"When a hacker mentions ‘life’, he is much more likely to mean this game than"
" the magazine, the breakfast cereal, or the human state of existence. Many "
"web resources are available starting from the `Open Directory page of Life "
"<http://dmoz.org/Computers/Artificial_Life/Cellular_Automata/Conway%27s_Game_of_Life/>`_."
" The `Life Lexicon <http://www.argentum.freeserve.co.uk/lex_home.htm>`_\\  "
"is a good indicator of what makes the game so fascinating."
msgstr ""
"John Horton Conwayが発明し、Martin Gardnerによって初めて公に紹介された(\\ *Scientific "
"American*\\ "
"、1970年10月号)セルオートマトンのゲーム。手作業でセルをシミュレートするのは面白くないので、このゲームの人気は、それを無理なくプレイできるコンピュータが現れるまで数年待たなければならなかった。多くのハッカーがこれに魅了される段階を通過し、各地のハッカーがこのゲームの数学的解析に大きく貢献した(最も顕著なのはMITのBill"
" Gosperで、彼はlifeを\\ :ref:`TECO`\\ "
"で実装すらした!)。ハッカーが‘life’に言及するとき、それは雑誌や朝食用シリアルや人間の生存状態よりも、このゲームを意味する可能性がはるかに高い。\\"
" `Open Directory page of Life "
"<http://dmoz.org/Computers/Artificial_Life/Cellular_Automata/Conway%27s_Game_of_Life/>`_\\"
" を起点として、多くのウェブリソースが利用できる。\\ `Life Lexicon "
"<http://www.argentum.freeserve.co.uk/lex_home.htm>`_\\ "
"は、このゲームをこれほど魅力的にしているものを示す良い指標である。"

#: ../../L/life.rst:20
msgid ""
"A glider, possibly the best known of the quasi-organic     phenomena in the "
"Game of Life."
msgstr "グライダー。おそらくGame of Lifeにおける擬似有機的な現象の中で最もよく知られたもの。"

